latestPosts.caption:
HARVARD CERTIFIED - 20 year old Chetali Would Cry 😭 

Back in 2019, when I started this journey, I had zero Instagram, zero social media family - just a quiet passion for skincare and a camera that barely captured what I saw in my head.

No plan. No promise. Just love for something that made people feel good in their skin

And today this… a solid certification from Harvard Medical School in Skincare. 

This isn’t just paper, it’s a piece of the path. A marker of the late nights, the silent wins, the slow but certain becoming.

If you’re starting small, unknown, or unsure - know this: it’s still possible.

Grateful doesn’t even begin to cover it 🧡📜

#StartedWithNothing #HarvardCertified #EmotionalWin #SkincareJourney #SlowGrowthStrongRoots

I have lived yet another dream today and I’m beyond grateful for it! 🙏❤️🧿

During my TEDx talk, I had the profound honor of delving into the depths of my personal journey, sharing the metamorphosis from a corporate professional to a flourishing entrepreneur. It was an exploration of the twists and turns, the triumphs and tribulations that shaped my path. With every anecdote shared, I aimed to illuminate the transformative power of resilience, perseverance, and unwavering determination. My hope was to inspire others to embark on their own journeys of self-discovery and entrepreneurial pursuit, knowing that with courage and conviction, they too can manifest their dreams into reality.

I extend my heartfelt gratitude to Taxila Business School for the gracious invitation and the incredible warmth and support they have shown us. It was truly an honor to be a part of such a welcoming community.

#tedtalk #tedtalks #tedex

latestPosts.caption:
🏅WE DID IT! WE WON 🏆the most prestigious ET Business Award for excellence in Entrepreneurship in Beauty & Skincare Industry and I’m absolutely speechless and overwhelmed. This recognition is an immense honor, marking the culmination of five years filled with grit, determination, and unwavering persistence. It’s been a journey marked by countless challenges, setbacks, and a whole lot of hard work—blood, sweat, and tears included. 

This recognition not only symbolizes the triumph of hard work but also the culmination of a passion-fueled journey. I extend my deepest gratitude to my incredible team and my audience, my biggest supporters who have been integral to this success. This award is as much yours as it is mine, I am incredibly grateful to each one of you who has been a part of this rather beautiful journey, supporting me every step of the way. Thank you for believing in my vision and for helping me reach this incredible milestone because nothing would have been possible without YOU!!

Here’s to many many more!

Grateful, blessed, humbled 🙏 #etwomenconclave2024

Happy Father’s Day ❤️

Today, we celebrate the two incredible fathers in our lives, the pillars of our little world.

To my father - my first hero. The one whose quiet strength has carried me through life’s storms and whose love has shaped the woman I am today. You’ve taught me resilience, patience, and what it means to love unconditionally. I’m forever grateful for the way you continue to stand by me, guiding me with your gentle wisdom and unwavering support.

And to my husband - the father of our daughter, the love of my life, and the rock of our family. Watching you with our little girl fills my heart in ways I never thought possible. Thank you for every bedtime story, every laugh, every lesson you teach her about kindness, courage, and dreaming big. She is so lucky to call you her papa and I am so blessed to walk this beautiful life with you by my side.

Strong fathers. Gentle hearts. Endless love.

Happy Father’s Day to the men who give us strength, keep us safe, and remind us every day what family truly means. We love you more than words could ever say. ❤️

#HappyFathersDay #BlessedWithTheBest #FamilyLove
